  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Fellows of the Same Year
  author: Jo Chung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In those days, the arena of letters rang with martial music,
    silver robes and blue sleeves adorned the rigid contest.
    Few can climb the blue clouds with steady steps—
    yet seeing your white hair, I have no face to show.

    The Black Secretariat's solemn authority shakes the mountains,
    praise from the Red Pivot reaches even the children.
    The Celestial Seal and Imperial Decree grant such honors—
    when will the ascent of fellow graduates ever cease?
  footnotes:
    - The Black Secretariat (烏府) and Red Pivot (鴻樞) are metaphorical references to high government offices and imperial authority.
    - The poem celebrates examination fellows who rose to prominence together, reflecting on shared ambition and the passage of time.
